<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3033] /= assignment operator breaks type system</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3033</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;while this works:&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; long d = 100L&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; d =  d / 33L&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; d.class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Result: class java.lang.Long&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the following breaks the type system and produces a Long that is a BigDecimal!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;groovy&amp;gt; long d = 100L&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; d /= 33L&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; d.class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Result: class java.math.BigDecimal&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
